{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "24", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "14", "M": "02", "S": "34"}}, "news": [{"title": "HC strikes down Tamil Nadu law giving registrars power to block property deals", "para": "Madras High Court has invalidated a Tamil Nadu amendment to the Registration Act, deeming it unconstitutional. The court ruled that Section 34-C, which allowed sub-registrars to block property registrations based on civil court matters, overstepped their authority. This provision, seen as a revival of earlier struck-down rules, infringed upon citizens' property rights and the doctrine of separation of powers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/madras-high-court-declares-tamil-nadus-property-registration-law-unconstitutional/131955277?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2355733/131955277.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Delhi extends slum rehabilitation cutoff year from 2015 to 2025", "para": "Delhi's slum rehabilitation scheme has been significantly expanded, with the cutoff date for eligibility extended to January 1, 2025. This landmark decision, approved by Home Minister Amit Shah, will now benefit lakhs of slum-dwellers, offering them modern housing with essential facilities. The move aligns with the Delhi Slum and JJ Cluster Rehabilitation and Relocation Policy, 2026, aiming to provide dignified living for families and boost the city's economy.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/delhi-extends-slum-rehabilitation-deadline-to-2025-aiding-thousands/131955263?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-163205/131955263.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "OCs for unfit buildings: 15 architects face blacklisting for violations in Haryana", "para": "Authorities are moving to blacklist 15 architects in Gurgaon following a major crackdown on irregularities in issuing occupation certificates. Investigations revealed buildings were certified as complete despite being unfinished, some even at the brickwork stage. This has raised serious questions about the self-certification policy for building approvals, with further penalties and disciplinary actions being considered.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/15-architects-face-blacklisting-over-occupation-certificate-violations-in-haryana/131954444?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-402496/131954444.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}